POSITION OVERVIEW
The Manufacturing Engineer is primarilyresponsible for the daily operations of the manufacturing unit, providingdetailed process and technical guidance for the Operations Team andidentifying, developing, and implementing process improvements.
TARGETED OUTCOMES
o Utilizing A2E (Six Sigma) processes, drive and coordinatecontinuous improvement efforts for area performance.
o Lead all machine transitions, customer complaintinvestigations, and OEE tracking for the department.
KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Manufacturing Engineer Duties
o Provide detailed process guidance for the Operations Teamin the execution of the production schedule
o Evaluate daily performance and identifies and eliminatesspecial cause variations
o Lead role in ensuring process parameters of existingprocess are in statistical control
o Through six-sigma, (A2E) approach, identify and reducecommon cause variations in the product and process
o Assure clearly defined procedures and instructions are documentedand issued to support the improvements developed by Process Engineers andTechnology
o Oversight of operations in identifying opportunities forimprovement
o Investigate and resolve process and product deviations
o Develop process changes to accommodate new products
o Provide support of and participate in project teams forfacilities improvements
o Routinely interact with Manufacturing Operators andsupervision, Maintenance Mechanics and supervision, Laboratory personnel,Project Engineering and Process Technology
o Maintain consistent product quality and customersatisfaction, reliable production volume and execution of the production plan
o Achieve outstanding safety performance and consistentenvironmental compliance
REQUIRED EXPERIENCE
o Bachelor of Science Degree in Chemical or MechanicalEngineering
DESIRED EXPERIENCE
o Knowledge and experience with the following is alsodesired: SPC, Provox DCS systems, PLC functionality
o Safety and environmental policies, KMS, Aspen IP21, NWAand Operator training
o Basic understanding of PSM, SPC and ISO9001 is alsopreferred
o Fiber Processing experience is preferred
o Minimum of 5+ years chemical or fiber manufacturingexperience is desired
